"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"072482136f0de5cdfab07de19c5557a9ff0db437","tid":2043049,"uid":298477,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-05-30T12:16:18.000Z","msg":"Punish China by offering the city&rsquo;s people a home in the U.K. and U.S.<br />\n<br />\nPres&shy;i&shy;dent Trump on Fri&shy;day is&shy;sued his re&shy;sponse to Chi&shy;na&rsquo;s as&shy;sault on Hong Kong&rsquo;s au&shy;ton&shy;omy, and as a state&shy;ment of sol&shy;i&shy;dar&shy;ity it was wel&shy;come. The prob&shy;lem is that the pun&shy;ish&shy;ment will fall mainly on the in&shy;no&shy;cent peo&shy;ple of Hong Kong rather than on the per&shy;pe&shy;tra&shy;tors in Bei&shy;jing. A bet&shy;ter idea would give Hong Kongers an es&shy;cape route to Amer&shy;ica.<br />\n<br />\nChina is re&shy;plac&shy;ing the &ldquo;one coun&shy;try, two sys&shy;tems&rdquo; form of gov&shy;er&shy;nance it promised Hong Kong with &ldquo;one coun&shy;try, one sys&shy;tem,&rdquo; Mr. Trump said in re&shy;marks at the White House. He&rsquo;s right. Bei&shy;jing has sig&shy;naled it will use a new na&shy;tional-se&shy;cu&shy;rity law to sti&shy;fle speech and pun&shy;ish dis&shy;senters. Du&shy;ti&shy;ful Hong Kong of&shy;fi&shy;cials might im&shy;ple&shy;ment the mea&shy;sures as a Potemkin for&shy;mal&shy;ity, but Bei&shy;jing will call the shots.<br />\n<br />\nMr. Trump said he&rsquo;ll use his au&shy;thor&shy;ity un&shy;der last year&rsquo;s Hong Kong Hu&shy;man Rights and Democ&shy;racy Act and re&shy;voke the city&rsquo;s spe&shy;cial trade and other priv&shy;i&shy;leges since it is no longer au&shy;tonomous. He wasn&rsquo;t spe&shy;cific, but the im&shy;pli&shy;ca&shy;tion is that Hong Kong will now be treated more or less the same as China. This could do par&shy;tic&shy;u&shy;lar harm to Hong Kong&rsquo;s sta&shy;tus as a fi&shy;nan&shy;cial cen&shy;ter, though the far greater dam&shy;age comes from Chi&shy;na&rsquo;s de&shy;ci&shy;sion to im&shy;pose Main&shy;land law&shy;less&shy;ness on the free ter&shy;ri&shy;tory.<br />\n<br />\nMr. Trump said he might also im&shy;pose sanc&shy;tions on Chi&shy;nese and Hong Kong of&shy;fi&shy;cials who im&shy;ple&shy;ment Chi&shy;na&rsquo;s new pol&shy;icy, and that has the virtue of hit&shy;ting the guilty. Yet none of this is likely to de&shy;ter Chi&shy;nese Pres&shy;i&shy;dent Xi Jin&shy;ping, who has de&shy;cided the Com&shy;mu&shy;nist Party can&rsquo;t tol&shy;er&shy;ate the ex&shy;am&shy;ple of Hong Kongers protest&shy;ing in the streets for po&shy;lit&shy;i&shy;cal free&shy;dom.<br />\n<br />\nWhich leads to an al&shy;ter&shy;na&shy;tive that would cause Bei&shy;jing heart&shy;burn: Of&shy;fer Hong Kong&rsquo;s peo&shy;ple green cards to live and work in the U.S. with a path to cit&shy;i&shy;zen&shy;ship if they want."},{"pid":"6ea9113904758fa978b5294d4476a152c285c858","tid":2043049,"uid":298477,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-05-30T12:17:08.000Z","msg":"Which leads to an al&shy;ter&shy;na&shy;tive that would cause Bei&shy;jing heart&shy;burn: Of&shy;fer Hong Kong&rsquo;s peo&shy;ple green cards to live and work in the U.S. with a path to cit&shy;i&shy;zen&shy;ship if they want.<br />\n<br />\nBritain has taken a large and com&shy;mend&shy;able step in this di&shy;rec&shy;tion. On Thurs&shy;day For&shy;eign Sec&shy;re&shy;tary Do&shy;minic Raab said that &ldquo;if China con&shy;tin&shy;ues down this path,&rdquo; some 350,000 Hong Kongers will be al&shy;lowed to stay longer and work in the U.K., &ldquo;and that will it&shy;self pro&shy;vide a path&shy;way to fu&shy;ture cit&shy;i&shy;zen&shy;ship.&rdquo; On Fri&shy;day the U.K. clar&shy;i&shy;fied that this could ap&shy;ply to some 2.9 mil&shy;lion British Na&shy;tion&shy;als (Over&shy;seas) in Hong Kong, which it ruled for some 150 years un&shy;til 1997.<br />\n<br />\nThe Trump Ad&shy;min&shy;is&shy;tra&shy;tion should also make visas avail&shy;able to Hong Kong peo&shy;ple who want to im&shy;mi&shy;grate to the U.S. Those who have protested in Hong Kong al&shy;ready have a &ldquo;well-founded fear of per&shy;se&shy;cu&shy;tion&rdquo; and would thus qual&shy;ify for asy&shy;lum un&shy;der the Im&shy;mi&shy;gra&shy;tion and Na&shy;tion&shy;al&shy;ity Act. Or they could be promptly ad&shy;mit&shy;ted un&shy;der a pro&shy;vi&shy;sion know as pa&shy;role un&shy;der the same law. Canada and Aus&shy;tralia joined the U.S. and Britain in a state&shy;ment of sol&shy;i&shy;dar&shy;ity this week, and they could of&shy;fer visas too.<br />\n<br />\nThis is the kind of Rea&shy;ganesque move that would re&shy;mind the world of Amer&shy;i&shy;ca&rsquo;s big heart and faith in free&shy;dom. It would cer&shy;tainly be heard in Bei&shy;jing, which would watch in hor&shy;ror as hun&shy;dreds of thou&shy;sands of Hong Kong Chi&shy;nese took up the visa of&shy;fers. The U.S. would ben&shy;e&shy;fit from a rush of new tal&shy;ent that is well ed&shy;u&shy;cated and en&shy;trepreneurial.<br />\n<br />\nThey wouldn&rsquo;t be look&shy;ing for a wel&shy;fare check. A Global En&shy;tre&shy;pre&shy;neur&shy;ship Mon&shy;i&shy;tor re&shy;port found in 2016 that one in five adults in Hong Kong planned to launch a busi&shy;ness within three years. Some 67% of Hong Kongers speak av&shy;er&shy;age, good or very good Eng&shy;lish, ac&shy;cord&shy;ing to a Jan&shy;uary re&shy;port by the Hong Kong Cen&shy;sus and Sta&shy;tistics De&shy;part&shy;ment. Amer&shy;i&shy;can flags have be&shy;come a reg&shy;u&shy;lar fea&shy;ture at protests in Hong Kong, which also en&shy;rages Bei&shy;jing."}]}